post_text:
Dear Families,

Now that the 2019-20 school year has concluded, our district is actively planning learning options for the start of the 2020-21 school year. There have been no formal adjustments to the school calendar at this point. We are also awaiting Ohio and Cuyahoga County guidelines for reopening, which should be unveiled in the next week or two. Your feedback will help us plan as we operate within the guidelines.

Much of our planning will focus on health guidelines and how we have to modify school and student groupings. We are also focused on improvements to our buildings. We will be installing air purification systems within each of our schools. These systems are both mercury‚Ä¶

post_text:
Independence Local Schools Hires James Hogue as Next Principal of Independence High School

At the June 4 Board of Education meeting, James (Jamie) Hogue was hired as the next principal of Independence High School (IHS). He replaces Bill McGuinness, who is eager for his next opportunity in returning to the classroom as a middle and high school teacher. Jamie begins his position as the new principal on August 1.

Hogue has been principal of Streetsboro High School since 2014. Prior to that, he was the assistant principal. He began his career in education as an English teacher. He received his Bachelor of Science (BS), English Language and Literature/Letters from John Carroll University. ‚Ä¶

Hogue has been principal of Streetsboro High School since 2014. Prior to that, he was the assistant principal. He began his career in education as an English teacher. He received his Bachelor of Science (BS), English Language and Literature/Letters from John Carroll University. ‚Ä¶

Independence Families,

I wanted to reach out with a quick update letting you know that just today, Governor DeWine extended Ohio‚Äôs school building closures through Friday, May 1.

We are committed to continuing the delivery of education through this time of building closures. Our staff has been working hard to develop and implement distance learning. We fully intend for this work to count for credit and grades as we continue to ‚Äúdo school.‚Äù Just last week, Ohio‚Äôs legislature passed House Bill 197 formalizing that distance learning replaces school during this time. Our hope is we can keep as much of our education progressing as possible.

Thank you for being our partners in this distance‚Ä¶

March 13, 2020

Dear Parents and Community,

Ohio Governor Mike DeWine gave the order yesterday afternoon for schools to close for three weeks to contain any spread of the coronavirus.

Independence Local Schools was already scheduled to have today, Friday, March 13 as a day off for students while staff worked on professional development. This will not change. I‚Äôm proud that our teachers have been working hard to prepare for distance learning opportunities, which will be our continued focus during the school closure.

There also will be no school Monday, March 16, however our school buildings will be open from 9 a.m. until 2 p.m. for students and parents to briefly stop in to pick up devices‚Ä¶

March 13, 2020

Dear Parents and Community,

Ohio Governor Mike DeWine gave the order yesterday afternoon for schools to close for three weeks to contain any spread of the coronavirus.

Independence Local Schools was already scheduled to have today, Friday, March 13 as a day off for students while staff worked on professional development. This will not change. I‚Äôm proud that our teachers have been working hard to prepare for distance learning opportunities, which will be our continued focus during the school closure.

There also will be no school Monday, March 16, however our school buildings will be open from 9 a.m. until 2 p.m. for students and parents to briefly stop in to pick up devices‚Ä¶

post_text:
This weekend the Independence Primary School Drama Club premiered its production of Annie: Kids! Two casts of 75 students performed for OVER 1,200 audience members!

The drama program is a true community effort, with dozens of parent volunteers building the set, making the costumes, and feeding 100 cast and crew members dinner for the entire tech week!

The IPS Drama Club is in its fourth year at Independence Primary School, and is funded by the IPS PTO. Thank you!

#iPride

post_text: We wanted to keep our community informed that the Independence Fire Department confirmed there was a backup of sewer gas at Independence High School today. The regular school day is continuing...all students are safe and back in classes.
